Nationalism or nationalism is an ideological movement of ideas that aims to win the interests of a particular nation, especially its sovereignty and self-government, and then to maintain it forever. argues that it is a legitimate source of political power. Nationalism has become the dominant style of political thought in Europe since the beginning of the 19th century and all over the world since the 20th century. In this period, the world political map was shaped according to the principles of nationalism. Today, it has a negative meaning in societies that adhere to the Anglo-Saxon culture and in circles advocating the idea of ​​the European Union.
